## Summary

This document records the **successful resolution of a â€œno sound / Dummy Outputâ€ issue**
that occurred after launching Google Chrome with custom GPU flags on **XFCE**.

The problem was **not Chrome itself**, but an **audio backend fallback to Dummy Output**
caused by PulseAudio losing track of the real sound device.

---

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ Environment

- OS: Linux
- Desktop Environment: XFCE (X11)
- Browser: Google Chrome (custom launch flags)
- Audio Backend: **PulseAudio (standalone)**
- PipeWire / WirePlumber: âŒ Not installed
- Hardware: Intel integrated audio

